><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rules Change Proposal: Religious Conversion</span><hr size=1> Actually, I miss SZ's player /con, too.<br>
<br>
I think that, at the very least, ShadowKnights and Paladins should have this ability (if VI wants to stick to the &quot;Detect Evil&quot; idea that AD&amp;D set forth for Paladins).  But I don't think it's outside the bounds of roleplay, either.  There should be something 'creepy' about evils that good people would detect, and there should be something 'sickeningly-sweet' about goods that evil people would detect.<br>
<br>
As for the Bracers on SZ, I don't care one way or another whether they come about on our server.  They're nice trinkets: +2 INT/WIS/STR (all three) and AC4 (or so), all for five platinum.  As something that displays your character's faith, they're nice, although for many Clerics and Druids, the various Symbols suffice.<br>
<br>
